CatDescriptText: Mary Mcleod Bethune was founder of Bethune Cookman College in Daytona Beach, Florida and one of the original members of the President Franklin D. Roosevelt's "Black Cabinet".
TitMainTitle: Group of women, including educator Mary Mcleod Bethune wearing large corsage standing behind microphone, and Jessie Vann; and three men, possibly including Alec Soapwell on far left, grouped around altar inside Warren Methodist Church with pipe organ
